Privacy Notice
PRIVACY POLICY
Last Revised: October 22, 2024
theSkimm, Inc. (“theSkimm” “we” or “us”) (“theSkimm” “we,” “us,” or “our”), know that data privacy is very important to you. We have created this privacy policy (the “Privacy Policy”) to describe what kinds of personal information we may obtain and process through:
· Our website (
https://www.theSkimm.com
) and our blog (blog.theskimm.com) (collectively, the “Site”);
· Our mobile application, which is accessible through tablets, smart phones, and other devices (the “App”);
· Any other website, mobile application, or digital property that links to this Privacy Policy, including but not limited to, our daily newsletter; and
· When you interact with us in person, electronically, or any other way.
By accessing or using the Site, the App, or any other website, web application, or digital property that links to this Privacy Policy (collectively, the “Digital Properties”), you may access or use our technology platform (“Platform”), our products and services, and/or open an account (each, an “Account”) (collectively, with the Platform and Digital Properties, the “Services”).
By accepting this Privacy Policy, accessing and/or using any Services, or otherwise manifesting your assent to this Privacy Policy, you agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy. If you are accepting this Privacy Policy on behalf of your employer or another organization, you hereby certify that you are authorized to bind such party to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to (or cannot comply with) all of the terms of this Privacy Policy, then you may not access or use the Services.
Capitalized terms that are not defined in this Privacy Policy have the meaning given them in the applicable Terms of Service or Terms of Use. BY ACCESSING AND/OR USING THE SERVICES, YOU SIGNIFY THAT YOU HAVE READ, UNDERSTOOD AND AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THIS PRIVACY POLICY, INCLUDING OUR TERMS OF SERVICE AND/OR TERMS OF USE, AS APPLICABLE, WHICH ARE INCORPORATED HEREIN BY REFERENCE.
IMPORTANT NOTICE TO RESIDENTS OF CERTAIN U.S. STATES
California Residents:
You may have additional rights regarding your personal information under the California Privacy Rights Act. Please review the
CPRA Privacy Notice
for further information.
